2026-04-16 12:04:11 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Ambient Sensor Module (relay contacts)'] hypothesis_explanation="All measurements upstream (from the power supply and into the ambient sensor module's relay coil circuit) are correct, with 12V supply present and correct relay trigger voltage. However, the voltage at the output side of the relay (the switch contacts to the load module) is a low value (~0.36V) when it should be near 12V, and this is true even when the lamp is off or on. The output from the relay is consistently not being fully connected to the supply, suggesting the relay contacts may be damaged (burnt, oxidized, or otherwise high-resistance/faulty), resulting in a large voltage drop across them and insufficient voltage being supplied to the load. This fits the symptom of the lamp cycling off briefly, potentially due to intermittent high resistance or poor contact at the relay. Replacing the relay or repairing the relay contacts inside the ambient sensor module should resolve this."
